File: A man waits to get a COVID-19 test done near Musina. AFP/Guillem Sartorio JOHANNESBURG - The country continues to see an increase in new COVID-19 infections. The health department said 3,084 cases have been recorded in the last 24 hours. Sadly, 72 people have succumbed to the virus, taking the death toll closer to 56,000. The country has over 41,000 active cases. Over 700,000 vaccines have been administered so far. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. As of today the cumulative number of #COVID19 in South Africa is 1 640 932 with 3 084 new cases reported
 In the last 24 hours, 102 deaths have been reported which brings the total to 55 976 deaths. Number of recoveries is 1 543 951 representing a recovery rate of 94,1% pic.twitter.com/eOcc6S601b